I managed to convince a random girl in my class that she was red/green colourblind. She was holding a red pencil and I asked if I could borrow her green one. So she goes to get a green one and I give her a strange look and ask her why she's giving me a red one. She asks me what I'm talking about, and I point to the pencil in her hand and tell her that I need that one. Everyone around me gets in on the joke and we referred to red as green and green as red for the rest of the day. Eventually I asked her if her eye doctor had diagnosed her as being colourblind and she started to believe that she actually was. Many lulz were had that day.
